<div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true" style="counter-reset:line-number 0"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><h2 id="pass-by-reference-vs-value" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#pass-by-reference-vs-value"><span>Pass by reference vs value</span></a></h2>
<p>All parameters (arguments) in the Python language are passed by reference. It means if you change what a parameter refers to within a function, the change also reflects back in the calling function. For example âˆ’</p>
